          <div  data-lhi="items[8]content" data-lh-lang data-lh-live-editor data-lhis="items-content">Customers must follow the battery maintenance guidelines provided in the user manual. Failure to do so may result in damage, which will void the warranty. ShopSolar Kits will not be held responsible for any resulting issues or costs.<br><br>


<b>Battery Maintenance Tips for Lithium-Based Batteries</b><br>
<ol>
<li data-lh-list><b>Keep it Charged:</b> To maintain optimal performance and longevity of your battery, aim to keep it charged above 20%. Avoid letting it fully discharge (down to 0%), as this can cause potential damage over time. Lithium-based batteries can be continually discharged to 100% depth of discharge and there is no long-term effect. However, we recommend you only discharge down to 80% to maintain better performance.</li><br>
<li data-lh-list><b>Avoid Extreme Temperatures:</b> Store and use batteries in moderate temperatures. Extreme heat can damage the battery, while extreme cold can reduce performance. Never store the product below -20 degrees Celsius or above 45 degrees Celsius. Operating temperature varies from one battery to another so always refer to the manufacturer’s manual.</li><br>

<li data-lh-list><b>Regular Use and Calibrate Occasionally:</b> Lithium batteries should be used regularly to keep the battery healthy. Long periods of inactivity can lead to capacity loss. Occasionally let your battery discharge fully and then recharge to 100%. This can help recalibrate the battery’s charge level indicator. This also ensures the battery’s BMS remains calibrated. </li><br>

<li data-lh-list><b>Use the Right Charger:</b> Always use the manufacturer’s recommended charger to avoid overcharging or damaging the battery.</li><br>

<li data-lh-list><b>Store Properly:</b> For long-term storage, please discharge the product every three months (firstly discharge it to 0%, then fully recharge it, and lastly discharge it to 60%)</li><br>

<li data-lh-list><b>Monitor for Damage:</b> Regularly check batteries for any signs of swelling, leaks, or damage. If you notice any issues, discontinue use immediately.</li><br>

<li data-lh-list><b>Avoid Overheating During Charging:</b> When charging, ensure the battery has good airflow. Avoid covering the device or placing it on soft surfaces that can trap heat. 
When in use, avoid using too many loads or over-discharging the battery to ensure that the draw is within the capacity of the unit and to avoid overheating.</li><br>

<li data-lh-list><b>Keep Contacts Clean:</b> Ensure that the battery contacts are clean and free of dirt or corrosion to maintain a good connection.</li><br>

<li data-lh-list><b>Educate Yourself:</b> Stay informed about best practices for your specific battery type and model, as recommendations can vary. </li>

</ol>
<br>
By following these tips, you can help prolong the lifespan and performance of your lithium-based batteries!</div>
